# HOW TO REVIEW
# -------------
# Each entry is pre-filled with the current translation from the locale .lproj.
# Edit the value in place where terminology or wording should change.
# # EN lines show English when it differs from the current value.
#
# Keep keys unchanged. Preserve %@, %ld, %1$@, \n, and keyboard symbols.
# Do not translate product names (Marked, CriticMarkup, etc.) unless
# your locale normally localizes them.
#
# Focus on consistency: Preview, Source, Export, Settings, Proofing,
# Statistics, Search, Table of Contents.
# See docs/LocalizationReviewGuide-short.md for priorities.
#
# Return this file with your edits (same filename).
# We merge with: python3 scripts/merge_localization_updates.py <this-file>
